# Service Layer Conventions

All HTTP / socket integrations live in `services/*.service.ts`. The fetch wrapper lives in `@/services/api-client.ts`.

## Always Use the Wrapper

```ts
import { apiRequest, apiMultipartRequest } from '@/services/api-client';

// JSON request
const post = await apiRequest<PostResponseDto>('/posts/' + id);

// JSON POST
await apiRequest<void>('/posts/' + id + '/like', { method: 'POST' });

// Multipart upload (DO NOT set Content-Type — fetch boundary)
const formData = new FormData();
formData.append('file', { uri, name, type } as any);
await apiMultipartRequest<MediaDto>('/media/upload', formData);
```

The wrapper:
- Reads `accessToken` from `AsyncStorage` and attaches `Authorization: Bearer ...`
- Unwraps `{ data | result | payload | user }` envelope automatically
- Calls `authService.handleUnauthorizedResponse` on 401
- Throws `Error(message)` on non-2xx

## Don'ts

```ts
// ❌ raw fetch — bypasses auth + envelope handling
const r = await fetch(`${API_URL}/posts`, { headers: { ... } });

// ❌ axios — not installed; do not add it
import axios from 'axios';

// ❌ React Query — not used in this project
import { useQuery } from '@tanstack/react-query';
```

## Service Class Shape

Services are classes exported as a singleton instance:

```ts
class PostService {
  async getById(id: string): Promise<PostResponseDto> {
    return apiRequest<PostResponseDto>(`/posts/${id}`);
  }

  async create(dto: CreatePostRequestDto): Promise<PostResponseDto> {
    return apiRequest<PostResponseDto>('/posts', {
      method: 'POST',
      body: JSON.stringify(dto),
    });
  }

  /** Normalize backend variability: `_id` vs `id`, missing arrays, etc. */
  private normalizePost(raw: unknown): PostResponseDto {
    if (!raw || typeof raw !== 'object') {
      throw new Error('Invalid post payload');
    }
    const r = raw as Record<string, unknown>;
    const id =
      (r.id as string | undefined) ??
      (r._id as { toString(): string } | undefined)?.toString() ??
      '';
    return { ...r, id } as PostResponseDto;
  }
}

export const postService = new PostService();
```

### Typing chaotic backend payloads

Prefer `unknown` + narrow, NOT `any`. If backend shape is genuinely unstable and narrowing is impractical, document the reason explicitly:

```ts
// eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any
private normalizeLegacy(raw: any): SomeDto {
  // raw: legacy /v1 endpoint, schema chưa ổn định — narrowing cost > benefit
  return { ...raw };
}
```

Pattern notes seen in this repo:
- DTO types come from `@/dtos` — import them, don't redefine
- Backend may return `_id` (Mongo) — normalize to `id` in services
- Vietnamese error messages OK (matches existing UX): `"Phản hồi từ máy chủ không hợp lệ"`

## Sockets

Real-time uses `socket.io-client`. Pattern: `*-socket.service.ts` (see `notification-socket.service.ts`). Always:
- Connect with auth token
- Clean up listeners on `disconnect`
- Expose typed event handlers, not raw `socket.on` calls
